KANO- Kano Chamber of Commerce, Mines, Industry, and Agriculture (KACCIMA) on Thursday begged the Federal Government to consider re-opening Mallam Aminu Kano International Airport (MAKIA) for international operations. Alhaji Abubakar Dalhatu, President, KACCIMA, told Reporters in Kano that continued closure has crippled the business and the economy of the 19 Northern states. According to him, this is the only international airport serving the entire 19 Northern states as he questioned the rational behind opening of Murtala Muhammed International Airport that serve the Southern part of the country. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Abubakar Dalhatu stated that businesses and individual travels have being incurring additional expenses, adding that intending travelers now settled for connecting flight to either Lagos or Abuja to connect their flight. He stressed that “We are indeed very worried about the continuing closure of the airport to international travels, especially now when the airlift of pilgrims for Umrah to Saudi Arabia have begun.” Recapitalisation: Law Union & Rock Insurance To Become Tangerine LUR Ibukun Awosika: Strategic Thinker, Hyperactive The KACCIMA boss stated that “Businesses in the sector are now being forced to convey their clients to Lagos and Abuja to make the journey. And we all know the security situation on the Kaduna -Abuja road these days.” “This is one of the reasons why we are calling on the Federal Government to consider the re- opening of the airport, to help rejuvenate the aviation sector in this part of the world”, Dalhatu pleaded.